•	“IoT without Security = Internet of Threat” – Stephanie Nappo. With the rise of Mirai Malware IoT devices, mainly, IP cameras are more prone to DDoS attacks, leveraging them as bots. 
•	Rise in Cryptojacking: We observed several crypto mining commands, signaling an increase in global cryptojacking attempts as attackers hijack devices for mining.
•	DDoS Attacks Surge: The US Central honeypot was hit with numerous DDoS attacks, likely driven by threat report by CrowdStrike and Mirai Malware combined. 

